Title: Lead Designer
Company Location: 19820 N 7th St, Phoenix, AZ, United States
Company Description:
Moon Valley Nursery is proud to be a family-owned and operated company. We are also a water-wise, eco-friendly, environmentally green company! We were founded in 1995 in a neighborhood north of downtown Phoenix known as “Moon Valley” and now have farming, retail, and landscaping operations throughout the southwest and across three time zones.  

Keeping things simple, our founder and CEO Les Blake began with a small location and the brilliant idea of providing high-quality trees and plants to his customers THE RIGHT WAY! As the customer base grew, so too did the demand for higher quantities and expanded services. 

Moon Valley Nursery thus began offering, “you buy it and we plant it” tree deals. We also started to provide more services such as everything from design through delivery and installation performed by our professional and dedicated nursery staff along with a one-of-a-kind tree warranty!
 
As the grower of its own massive inventory of trees, plants, palms and more, Moon Valley continues to set the industry standard for the highest quality, hardiest, and most aesthetically pleasing products. Over the years, Moon Valley Nurseries has expanded across the Southwest, now featuring retail and growing operations in Arizona, California, Nevada, and Texas.

Recently, Moon Valley Nurseries acquired all inventory, production facilities and assets of Growest Nurseries in Palm Springs and Riverside, California; Glen Flora Farms in Katy Texas; and other well established regional nursery operations.

Moon Valley Nurseries is now the largest grower of box trees and palms in North America.
 
We live by one simple rule:  Bigger trees, better service, and always the best price… Guaranteed!!!

Title: Head of Business Systems
Company Location: 832 W 22nd St, Tempe, AZ 85282, United States
Company Description:
Since 2006, DBL has worked with property managers across the Phoenix metro area to exceed their expectations, proactively meet their needs by delivering high-quality, timely landscaping service.

After working his way up the career ladder at his parents’ commercial landscaping company, DBL Founder Aric Budden saw a new opportunity to build a company that would deliver more than landscaping services to his clients – it would be a partnership to make their jobs easier. With only a pick-up truck and a few tools, Aric started DBL as a residential landscaping company and began building a strong company culture based on several core values:

•  Service and people before profits
•  Sense of urgency
•  Be humble
•  Do more with less
•  Embrace simplicity

Using these values as a guide, Aric built a team of dependable professionals and eventually transitioned to a complete focus on commercial landscaping for professionally-managed offices, industrial, medical, and retail properties.

Although many things about DBL have evolved over time, one thing has stayed the same: a singular focus on not only providing the best service, but also being a true partner to our clients and employees every step of the way.

Follow our page for an inside look at what it’s like to work with DBL, along with our most recent job openings.

Title: Concrete Superintendent
Company Location: 4750 N La Cholla Blvd, Tucson, AZ 85705-4852, United States
Company Description:
Established in 2001, Eagle Rock Excavating, LLC is a Tucson, Arizona based civil construction company specializing in full site development including but not limited to storm water pollution prevention (SWPP), excavation, sewer installation, water installation, dry utilities, storm water drainage, riprap, seal coating, asphalt paving, and site concrete work. Our management team has more than 70 years of cumulative experience in commercial, institutional, public works, residential subdivision and retail property development. 

We're a Tucson based company with strong roots. Our team is led by Matthew Hazen, a University of Arizona graduate in Civil Engineering. We are affiliated with Ventana Landscaping and Canyon Building & Design, a Tucson company that has built a reputation for providing smart, quality construction that compliments the beauty of the Sonoran Desert. 

At Eagle Rock, we are a solutions-driven organization that seeks to establish mutually beneficial relationships with our clients through value engineering, conceptual planning, and on demand emergency response. We understand that a successful project is one that is completed on time and within  budget parameters. Eagle Rock has earned a solid reputation for the way we run our business

Title: Senior Engineering Technician
Company Location: 5624 N 54th Ave, Glendale, AZ 85301, United States
Company Description:
A subsidiary of Natives of Kodiak (NOK), Stormwater Plans, LLC DBA SWP Contracting & Paving (SWP) is a fiscally-sound Alaskan Native Company that participates in the Small Business Administration’s Section 8(a) Business Development Program and is HUBZone certified. SWP offers its customers excellent construction and services at competitive prices.

The Company was founded in 2005 on the principle that the client is the number one stakeholder in any project. It is our belief that a project can be profitable while still providing a 100% client satisfaction rating by ensuring that the needs of the client are the priority. Initially started as a civil engineering and consulting firm, SWP evolved from a specialty stormwater contractor, and now has a renewed focus as a general contractor throughout the Southwest.

Scopes of work include: site grading and civil work, drainage structures, retention basins, sewer trenches, infrastructure installation and reconstruction, concrete structures and flatwork, roadway construction, milling, crack sealing, chip seal, paving, striping, emergency pavement repair, airport runway and taxiway construction, railway construction, bridge construction, bridge rehabilitation, and concrete repairs, work within ADOT ROW, soil cement bank protection, channel excavation, riprap, wet and dry utilities, electric improvements, and landscaping improvements.

For more information visit our website, www.swpcontracting.com, or contact us at 623.544.7305

Like us on facebook! https://www.facebook.com/SWPcontractingandpaving/

Our management team has more than 70 years of cumulative experience in commercial, institutional, public works, residential subdivision and retail property development.

Title: Sales Project Manager
Company Location: 4320 W Blvd Ste 1, Chandler, AZ 85226, United States
Company Description:
California Pools & Landscape is Arizona's premier outdoor living solution, and our swimming pools are designed with Arizona families in mind. With over 31 years in the Phoenix area, and over 30,000 swimming pools and spas in the ground without a single ROC complaint, we understand how a pool fits into a family's lifestyle and enhances Arizona's landscaping.

We also know that no two families are exactly alike. That’s why we begin the pool and landscape process with a conversation – to learn what you want in a pool and how you use your backyard. After we fully understand your needs, we provide clear and complete information on features, construction time and costs. Then, throughout the build, we keep you informed of the process, and we enforce the strictest safety standards to keep your family and our craftsmen safe. That's why we're Arizona's preferred backyard builder.

Title: General Manager
Company Location: 19820 N 7th St, Phoenix, AZ, United States
Company Description:
Moon Valley Nursery is proud to be a family-owned and operated company. We are also a water-wise, eco-friendly, environmentally green company! We were founded in 1995 in a neighborhood north of downtown Phoenix known as “Moon Valley” and now have farming, retail, and landscaping operations throughout the southwest and across three time zones.  

Keeping things simple, our founder and CEO Les Blake began with a small location and the brilliant idea of providing high-quality trees and plants to his customers THE RIGHT WAY! As the customer base grew, so too did the demand for higher quantities and expanded services. 

Moon Valley Nursery thus began offering, “you buy it and we plant it” tree deals. We also started to provide more services such as everything from design through delivery and installation performed by our professional and dedicated nursery staff along with a one-of-a-kind tree warranty!
 
As the grower of its own massive inventory of trees, plants, palms and more, Moon Valley continues to set the industry standard for the highest quality, hardiest, and most aesthetically pleasing products. Over the years, Moon Valley Nurseries has expanded across the Southwest, now featuring retail and growing operations in Arizona, California, Nevada, and Texas.

Recently, Moon Valley Nurseries acquired all inventory, production facilities and assets of Growest Nurseries in Palm Springs and Riverside, California; Glen Flora Farms in Katy Texas; and other well established regional nursery operations.

Moon Valley Nurseries is now the largest grower of box trees and palms in North America.
 
We live by one simple rule:  Bigger trees, better service, and always the best price… Guaranteed!!!

Title: V.P
Company Location: 1401 N 29th Ave, Phoenix, AZ 85009, United States
Company Description: Established in 1960, Paul Sexton Sr. began this business with these principals in mind: integrity, passion, innovation, and an uncompromising commitment to complete customer satisfaction. It is with that same vision and conviction, Kent Sexton Jr. (Owner/President), since 1986, has led and directed Sexton Pest Control to become one of the largest and well respected pest control companies in Arizona. We attribute our success to three key areas. First, committed, caring, and knowledgeable team members whose dedication, passion, and pursuit for excellence in exceeding the customer’s expectations is unparalleled in our industry. Second, innovative pest management programs such as Sexton Pest Control’s Centralized Pest Control System, an in-wall tubing system that virtually eliminates the customer from product exposure addresses pests directly where they harbor. We also offer the Total Pest Protection Plan, an all-inclusive pest program. Additional services include weeds, birds, pests, termites, handyman, landscaping, heating and air conditioning, exclusionary programs and more. Third and most importantly, we attribute our success to our loyal customers and their referrals. Sexton Pest Control continues to commit itself to be an industry leader, not only in service, but also in overall customer satisfaction.

Company Location: 19820 N 7th St, Phoenix, AZ, United States
Company Description:
Moon Valley Nursery is proud to be a family-owned and operated company. We are also a water-wise, eco-friendly, environmentally green company! We were founded in 1995 in a neighborhood north of downtown Phoenix known as “Moon Valley” and now have farming, retail, and landscaping operations throughout the southwest and across three time zones.  

Keeping things simple, our founder and CEO Les Blake began with a small location and the brilliant idea of providing high-quality trees and plants to his customers THE RIGHT WAY! As the customer base grew, so too did the demand for higher quantities and expanded services. 

Moon Valley Nursery thus began offering, “you buy it and we plant it” tree deals. We also started to provide more services such as everything from design through delivery and installation performed by our professional and dedicated nursery staff along with a one-of-a-kind tree warranty!
 
As the grower of its own massive inventory of trees, plants, palms and more, Moon Valley continues to set the industry standard for the highest quality, hardiest, and most aesthetically pleasing products. Over the years, Moon Valley Nurseries has expanded across the Southwest, now featuring retail and growing operations in Arizona, California, Nevada, and Texas.

Recently, Moon Valley Nurseries acquired all inventory, production facilities and assets of Growest Nurseries in Palm Springs and Riverside, California; Glen Flora Farms in Katy Texas; and other well established regional nursery operations.

Moon Valley Nurseries is now the largest grower of box trees and palms in North America.
 
We live by one simple rule:  Bigger trees, better service, and always the best price… Guaranteed!!!

Title: Site Superintendent

Company Description:
Established in 2001, Eagle Rock Excavating, LLC is a Tucson, Arizona based civil construction company specializing in full site development including but not limited to storm water pollution prevention (SWPP), excavation, sewer installation, water installation, dry utilities, storm water drainage, riprap, seal coating, asphalt paving, and site concrete work. Our management team has more than 70 years of cumulative experience in commercial, institutional, public works, residential subdivision and retail property development. 

We're a Tucson based company with strong roots. Our team is led by Matthew Hazen, a University of Arizona graduate in Civil Engineering. We are affiliated with Ventana Landscaping and Canyon Building & Design, a Tucson company that has built a reputation for providing smart, quality construction that compliments the beauty of the Sonoran Desert. 

At Eagle Rock, we are a solutions-driven organization that seeks to establish mutually beneficial relationships with our clients through value engineering, conceptual planning, and on demand emergency response. We understand that a successful project is one that is completed on time and within  budget parameters. Eagle Rock has earned a solid reputation for the way we run our business

Title: HR Director
Company Location: 832 W 22nd St, Tempe, AZ 85282, United States
Company Description:
Since 2006, DBL has worked with property managers across the Phoenix metro area to exceed their expectations, proactively meet their needs by delivering high-quality, timely landscaping service.

After working his way up the career ladder at his parents’ commercial landscaping company, DBL Founder Aric Budden saw a new opportunity to build a company that would deliver more than landscaping services to his clients – it would be a partnership to make their jobs easier. With only a pick-up truck and a few tools, Aric started DBL as a residential landscaping company and began building a strong company culture based on several core values:

•  Service and people before profits
•  Sense of urgency
•  Be humble
•  Do more with less
•  Embrace simplicity

Using these values as a guide, Aric built a team of dependable professionals and eventually transitioned to a complete focus on commercial landscaping for professionally-managed offices, industrial, medical, and retail properties.

Although many things about DBL have evolved over time, one thing has stayed the same: a singular focus on not only providing the best service, but also being a true partner to our clients and employees every step of the way.

Follow our page for an inside look at what it’s like to work with DBL, along with our most recent job openings.

Title: Regional Sales Manager
Contact Location: California, san diego county, United States
Company Location: 19820 N 7th St, Phoenix, AZ, United States
Company Description:
Moon Valley Nursery is proud to be a family-owned and operated company. We are also a water-wise, eco-friendly, environmentally green company! We were founded in 1995 in a neighborhood north of downtown Phoenix known as “Moon Valley” and now have farming, retail, and landscaping operations throughout the southwest and across three time zones.  

Keeping things simple, our founder and CEO Les Blake began with a small location and the brilliant idea of providing high-quality trees and plants to his customers THE RIGHT WAY! As the customer base grew, so too did the demand for higher quantities and expanded services. 

Moon Valley Nursery thus began offering, “you buy it and we plant it” tree deals. We also started to provide more services such as everything from design through delivery and installation performed by our professional and dedicated nursery staff along with a one-of-a-kind tree warranty!
 
As the grower of its own massive inventory of trees, plants, palms and more, Moon Valley continues to set the industry standard for the highest quality, hardiest, and most aesthetically pleasing products. Over the years, Moon Valley Nurseries has expanded across the Southwest, now featuring retail and growing operations in Arizona, California, Nevada, and Texas.

Recently, Moon Valley Nurseries acquired all inventory, production facilities and assets of Growest Nurseries in Palm Springs and Riverside, California; Glen Flora Farms in Katy Texas; and other well established regional nursery operations.

Moon Valley Nurseries is now the largest grower of box trees and palms in North America.
 
We live by one simple rule:  Bigger trees, better service, and always the best price… Guaranteed!!!

Title: President
Company Location: 832 W 22nd St, Tempe, AZ 85282, United States
Company Description:
Since 2006, DBL has worked with property managers across the Phoenix metro area to exceed their expectations, proactively meet their needs by delivering high-quality, timely landscaping service.

After working his way up the career ladder at his parents’ commercial landscaping company, DBL Founder Aric Budden saw a new opportunity to build a company that would deliver more than landscaping services to his clients – it would be a partnership to make their jobs easier. With only a pick-up truck and a few tools, Aric started DBL as a residential landscaping company and began building a strong company culture based on several core values:

•  Service and people before profits
•  Sense of urgency
•  Be humble
•  Do more with less
•  Embrace simplicity

Using these values as a guide, Aric built a team of dependable professionals and eventually transitioned to a complete focus on commercial landscaping for professionally-managed offices, industrial, medical, and retail properties.

Although many things about DBL have evolved over time, one thing has stayed the same: a singular focus on not only providing the best service, but also being a true partner to our clients and employees every step of the way.

Follow our page for an inside look at what it’s like to work with DBL, along with our most recent job openings.

Title: Manager
Company Location: 19820 N 7th St, Phoenix, AZ, United States
Company Description:
Moon Valley Nursery is proud to be a family-owned and operated company. We are also a water-wise, eco-friendly, environmentally green company! We were founded in 1995 in a neighborhood north of downtown Phoenix known as “Moon Valley” and now have farming, retail, and landscaping operations throughout the southwest and across three time zones.  

Keeping things simple, our founder and CEO Les Blake began with a small location and the brilliant idea of providing high-quality trees and plants to his customers THE RIGHT WAY! As the customer base grew, so too did the demand for higher quantities and expanded services. 

Moon Valley Nursery thus began offering, “you buy it and we plant it” tree deals. We also started to provide more services such as everything from design through delivery and installation performed by our professional and dedicated nursery staff along with a one-of-a-kind tree warranty!
 
As the grower of its own massive inventory of trees, plants, palms and more, Moon Valley continues to set the industry standard for the highest quality, hardiest, and most aesthetically pleasing products. Over the years, Moon Valley Nurseries has expanded across the Southwest, now featuring retail and growing operations in Arizona, California, Nevada, and Texas.

Recently, Moon Valley Nurseries acquired all inventory, production facilities and assets of Growest Nurseries in Palm Springs and Riverside, California; Glen Flora Farms in Katy Texas; and other well established regional nursery operations.

Moon Valley Nurseries is now the largest grower of box trees and palms in North America.
 
We live by one simple rule:  Bigger trees, better service, and always the best price… Guaranteed!!!

Title: Texas Auditor
Company Location: 19820 N 7th St, Phoenix, AZ, United States
Company Description:
Moon Valley Nursery is proud to be a family-owned and operated company. We are also a water-wise, eco-friendly, environmentally green company! We were founded in 1995 in a neighborhood north of downtown Phoenix known as “Moon Valley” and now have farming, retail, and landscaping operations throughout the southwest and across three time zones.  

Keeping things simple, our founder and CEO Les Blake began with a small location and the brilliant idea of providing high-quality trees and plants to his customers THE RIGHT WAY! As the customer base grew, so too did the demand for higher quantities and expanded services. 

Moon Valley Nursery thus began offering, “you buy it and we plant it” tree deals. We also started to provide more services such as everything from design through delivery and installation performed by our professional and dedicated nursery staff along with a one-of-a-kind tree warranty!
 
As the grower of its own massive inventory of trees, plants, palms and more, Moon Valley continues to set the industry standard for the highest quality, hardiest, and most aesthetically pleasing products. Over the years, Moon Valley Nurseries has expanded across the Southwest, now featuring retail and growing operations in Arizona, California, Nevada, and Texas.

Recently, Moon Valley Nurseries acquired all inventory, production facilities and assets of Growest Nurseries in Palm Springs and Riverside, California; Glen Flora Farms in Katy Texas; and other well established regional nursery operations.

Moon Valley Nurseries is now the largest grower of box trees and palms in North America.
 
We live by one simple rule:  Bigger trees, better service, and always the best price… Guaranteed!!!

Title: Regional Operations Manager
Company Location: 19820 N 7th St, Phoenix, AZ, United States
Company Description:
Moon Valley Nursery is proud to be a family-owned and operated company. We are also a water-wise, eco-friendly, environmentally green company! We were founded in 1995 in a neighborhood north of downtown Phoenix known as “Moon Valley” and now have farming, retail, and landscaping operations throughout the southwest and across three time zones.  

Keeping things simple, our founder and CEO Les Blake began with a small location and the brilliant idea of providing high-quality trees and plants to his customers THE RIGHT WAY! As the customer base grew, so too did the demand for higher quantities and expanded services. 

Moon Valley Nursery thus began offering, “you buy it and we plant it” tree deals. We also started to provide more services such as everything from design through delivery and installation performed by our professional and dedicated nursery staff along with a one-of-a-kind tree warranty!
 
As the grower of its own massive inventory of trees, plants, palms and more, Moon Valley continues to set the industry standard for the highest quality, hardiest, and most aesthetically pleasing products. Over the years, Moon Valley Nurseries has expanded across the Southwest, now featuring retail and growing operations in Arizona, California, Nevada, and Texas.

Recently, Moon Valley Nurseries acquired all inventory, production facilities and assets of Growest Nurseries in Palm Springs and Riverside, California; Glen Flora Farms in Katy Texas; and other well established regional nursery operations.

Moon Valley Nurseries is now the largest grower of box trees and palms in North America.
 
We live by one simple rule:  Bigger trees, better service, and always the best price… Guaranteed!!!

Title: LANDSCAPER
Company Location: 36815 N Cave Creek Road, Cave Creek, AZ 85331, United States
Company Description:
Desert Foothills Landscape has become synonymous with large scale, awe inspiring, high desert landscapes. We have had the honor of creating beautiful unique surroundings for private residences and museums alike. We have won awards, graced magazine pages, and appeared on television, but ultimately, we just love what we do.

We have literally moved mountains, boulder by boulder, to make dreams come true. We are just that passionate about exceeding our clients' expectations!

Since our inception in 1990, we have honed an innovative artistic approach to creating outdoor living environments that will significantly increase the value of your property, and more importantly, the quality of your life.

We create the art you live within. We view landscape as an interaction, multidimensional, living art form. It should be unique, stimulating setting that engages the senses, sparks your imagination, and renews your spirit. Your landscape should have a timeless beauty that allows you to transcend the day-to-day, and greatly enhance your quality of life. We want you to awake in the morning with a desire to race outside to your own personal oasis.

Over the years, we have fine-tuned our artistic approach to landscape design and installation. Our techniques are based on decades of successful installations that began small and grew over time to an impressive “WOW FACTOR” scale. We have built up an extensive palette to work with and we are able to pull from it on site to create vignettes as we go. In the beginning stages, we walk you through a clear plan of the elevations in the yard and the placement of the focal vignettes that will create the flow through your landscape journey.

Company Description:
McGann & Associates is a Tucson, Arizona based professional landscape architectural firm.  Established in 1984, the firm has 32 years of experience on a wide range of landscape architectural, park planning, and sports field development projects in southern Arizona.  Representative clients include; the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers, Arizona State Parks, the University of Arizona, Pima Community College, Pima County, and the communities of Tucson, Tempe, Casa Grande, Sierra Vista, Nogales, Marana, and Oro Valley.

McGann & Associates and Pima County have successfully collaborated on numerous occasions.  Collaborative efforts include the planning and design of urban / active recreation parks, the design of linear parks and trail systems, and the planning of natural resource areas.  Specific project examples include Brandi Fenton Memorial Park, the Rillito River Park (Flowing Wells to La Cholla), and Tortolita Mountain Park.  McGann & Associates’ work for Pima County also includes the preparation of the “Standard Details and Specifications for Park Improvements” document which will apply to the Northside Regional Park project.

McGann & Associates also has a long-standing relationship with GLHN Architects and Engineers.  The firms have collaborated on more than 100 projects over the past 25 years.  Project examples include the University of Arizona Women’s Soccer Field, Crossroads at Silverbell Park, and the new lighted soccer fields at Morris K. Udall Regional Park.

McGann & Associates staff includes three Arizona registered landscape architects.  These individuals are supported by designers, CAD technicians, and clerical staff all of whom are familiar with Pima County’s standards, policies, and procedures.

Title: Vice President of Customer Success
Company Location: 2801 E Camelback Rd Suite 200, Phoenix, AZ, United States
Company Description:
➤ Business leaders often don’t leverage technology as the catalyst to scale. In fact, it is frequently their technology that prevents them from scaling effectively. The landscape of IT has changed. The traditional approach of fixing problems as they arise has been replaced with proactively building solutions to prevent them from happening.

Most current IT environments, even those run by top technology leaders, are struggling with the evolution of software, making it difficult to implement the right solutions. As a result, they tend to stick to the status quo, which ultimately suppresses company growth.

With this evolution it is now easier for businesses to participate in the configuration of software solutions. This introduces the ability to affordably customize and meet the needs of each company’s specific business process. 

With the right team and the right approach, leadership, IT and end users can collaborate to deliver a long-term platform solution. This better serves all of the stakeholders and leads to more satisfied customers.

➤ The answer is one centralized platform in combination with an agile roadmap, influenced by these stakeholders. 

No one knows your business better than your people, yet companies pay consultants to build a solution without enabling their existing talent, resulting in frustration and limited adoption.

Title: Chief Curriculum Officer
Company Location: 15029 N Thompson Peak Pkwy, Scottsdale, AZ, United States
Company Description:
ARI has stepped into the education arena to venture where few others have gone; yet, where there is such an overwhelming need. ARI brings a focused education practice that affirms the presence of both practicality and up-to-date knowledge on the ever-changing Social Media world.

WHAT MAKES ARI DIFFERENT?

ARI is driven by the desire to bring education to two distinct niches, each of which is growing rapidly yet being underserved. One is the student who demands to learn how to apply social media into a business context while doing so rapidly and without all the extra “fluff” and time that traditionally goes along with education. Second, is the business (large and small) in need of quickly getting staff up to speed in skills that are taught with both academic rigor and up-to-date techniques.

At the core of what ARI believes, develops, and practices is the creation of teaching methods that must involve several key components. These are practicality supported by experience vs. just theory; engagement and relevance while learning; and, active, persistent measurements to increase knowledge retention during and after the courses.

A specialty of ARI has been to research the current and constantly changing landscape of the social media world. This includes both technology, societal changes, routine platform changes, and regulatory requirements. The fast-paced nature of social media has been an obstacle to successful teaching with educational entities. ARI has come to specialize on keeping its finger on the pulse of these changes and, maintaining the network of currently practicing professionals that are vital to its teaching.

Title: Founder/CEO
Company Location: 111 W Monroe St Suite 1220, Phoenix, AZ 85003, United States
Company Description:
I founded my company, phx-IT, in 2003 on a simple concept. Most companies and their staff prefer to have an IT person that is PERSONABLE and PRESENT onsite to handle their technology needs. Instead of waiting for problems to arise, we visit each customer at regular intervals throughout the week and handle their needs while onsite. As we’ve grown we’ve scaled this same model to having technicians visit our clients’ offices on a set schedule multiple times each week. We feel that understanding our customers’ technology needs REQUIRES our presence. This doesn’t mean we’re not available to remotely assist. Rather, remote support is added value to each of our customers instead of being the primary service. 

Over the past 10 years IT support companies have gradually been placed into 2 separate categories, Break/Fix and Managed Service Providers. I think there is a better way of doing business. 

The Break/Fix model 
This provides IT support at an hourly rate when a customer has a problem. These providers typically aren’t proactive about preventing problems but tend to be very good firefighters in emergencies.

MSP’s (Managed Service Providers) provide preventative maintenance on systems and charge a fee per server and workstation (or per user). They work almost entirely remotely and are very proactive but charge a higher rate if they ever have to be onsite, which they typically avoid at all costs since their pricing/service model simply doesn’t take into account the value of being onsite.

As we’ve grown, we’ve added all of tools that our competitors use to allow us to provide a high level of service and give us an advantage in the ever changing IT landscape. The major difference is, we don’t charge our customers a monthly rate for the tools we use. We see these tools as necessary to do our jobs and keep our clients safe and secure.  

I am passionate about the way we do business and know that our company’s most valuable possession is our reputation.

Title: Help Desk Lead
Company Location: 111 W Monroe St Suite 1220, Phoenix, AZ 85003, United States
Company Description:
I founded my company, phx-IT, in 2003 on a simple concept. Most companies and their staff prefer to have an IT person that is PERSONABLE and PRESENT onsite to handle their technology needs. Instead of waiting for problems to arise, we visit each customer at regular intervals throughout the week and handle their needs while onsite. As we’ve grown we’ve scaled this same model to having technicians visit our clients’ offices on a set schedule multiple times each week. We feel that understanding our customers’ technology needs REQUIRES our presence. This doesn’t mean we’re not available to remotely assist. Rather, remote support is added value to each of our customers instead of being the primary service. 

Over the past 10 years IT support companies have gradually been placed into 2 separate categories, Break/Fix and Managed Service Providers. I think there is a better way of doing business. 

The Break/Fix model 
This provides IT support at an hourly rate when a customer has a problem. These providers typically aren’t proactive about preventing problems but tend to be very good firefighters in emergencies.

MSP’s (Managed Service Providers) provide preventative maintenance on systems and charge a fee per server and workstation (or per user). They work almost entirely remotely and are very proactive but charge a higher rate if they ever have to be onsite, which they typically avoid at all costs since their pricing/service model simply doesn’t take into account the value of being onsite.

As we’ve grown, we’ve added all of tools that our competitors use to allow us to provide a high level of service and give us an advantage in the ever changing IT landscape. The major difference is, we don’t charge our customers a monthly rate for the tools we use. We see these tools as necessary to do our jobs and keep our clients safe and secure.  

I am passionate about the way we do business and know that our company’s most valuable possession is our reputation.

Company Description:
➤ Business leaders often don’t leverage technology as the catalyst to scale. In fact, it is frequently their technology that prevents them from scaling effectively. The landscape of IT has changed. Title: Creative Director
Company Location: 15029 N Thompson Peak Pkwy, Scottsdale, AZ, United States
Company Description:
ARI has stepped into the education arena to venture where few others have gone; yet, where there is such an overwhelming need. ARI brings a focused education practice that affirms the presence of both practicality and up-to-date knowledge on the ever-changing Social Media world.

WHAT MAKES ARI DIFFERENT?

ARI is driven by the desire to bring education to two distinct niches, each of which is growing rapidly yet being underserved. One is the student who demands to learn how to apply social media into a business context while doing so rapidly and without all the extra “fluff” and time that traditionally goes along with education. Second, is the business (large and small) in need of quickly getting staff up to speed in skills that are taught with both academic rigor and up-to-date techniques.

At the core of what ARI believes, develops, and practices is the creation of teaching methods that must involve several key components. These are practicality supported by experience vs. just theory; engagement and relevance while learning; and, active, persistent measurements to increase knowledge retention during and after the courses.

A specialty of ARI has been to research the current and constantly changing landscape of the social media world. This includes both technology, societal changes, routine platform changes, and regulatory requirements. The fast-paced nature of social media has been an obstacle to successful teaching with educational entities. ARI has come to specialize on keeping its finger on the pulse of these changes and, maintaining the network of currently practicing professionals that are vital to its teaching.

Title: Vice President of Marketing and Passenger Services
Company Location: 300 North Broadway, Clarkdale, AZ 86324, United States
Company Description:
Verde Canyon Railroad: Arizona’s Longest-Running Nature Show

Located in the red rock country near Sedona, Verde Canyon Railroad’s rare ribbon of rails runs through a dramatic high desert landscape adjacent to a precious riparian ecosystem. Since 1912 this heritage railroad, sandwiched between two protected national forests, has existed in harmony in the wilderness through which it passes and the canyon’s native inhabitants. The scenic excursion first launched in 1990, offering a glimpse of this treasured landscape to visitors while providing an unforgettable encounter that transcends generations. 

The Verde Canyon Railroad’s four-hour rail trip takes passengers on a 20-mile journey through exciting geology swathed in railroad history. Three types of accommodations make up the Verde Canyon Railroad – caboose, first-class and coach-class. Every passenger has two seats to enjoy – one inside with easy access to another on an open-air viewing car. All attendants, well-versed in the canyon’s history, geology and wildlife, share highlights and answer questions.

One of the highlights of the Verde Canyon Railroad journey is seeing bald eagles. Through the years, eagles have nested in the canyon and cohabited with the daily passing of the train, much to the delight of passengers and crews. The population of eagles swells in the Verde Canyon during nesting season between December and March when resident birds are joined by migrating winter visitors.

Title: Chief Information Security Officer
Company Location: 111 W Monroe St Suite 1220, Phoenix, AZ 85003, United States
Company Description:
I founded my company, phx-IT, in 2003 on a simple concept. Most companies and their staff prefer to have an IT person that is PERSONABLE and PRESENT onsite to handle their technology needs. Instead of waiting for problems to arise, we visit each customer at regular intervals throughout the week and handle their needs while onsite. As we’ve grown we’ve scaled this same model to having technicians visit our clients’ offices on a set schedule multiple times each week. We feel that understanding our customers’ technology needs REQUIRES our presence. This doesn’t mean we’re not available to remotely assist. Rather, remote support is added value to each of our customers instead of being the primary service. 

Over the past 10 years IT support companies have gradually been placed into 2 separate categories, Break/Fix and Managed Service Providers. I think there is a better way of doing business. 

The Break/Fix model 
This provides IT support at an hourly rate when a customer has a problem. These providers typically aren’t proactive about preventing problems but tend to be very good firefighters in emergencies.

MSP’s (Managed Service Providers) provide preventative maintenance on systems and charge a fee per server and workstation (or per user). They work almost entirely remotely and are very proactive but charge a higher rate if they ever have to be onsite, which they typically avoid at all costs since their pricing/service model simply doesn’t take into account the value of being onsite.

As we’ve grown, we’ve added all of tools that our competitors use to allow us to provide a high level of service and give us an advantage in the ever changing IT landscape. The major difference is, we don’t charge our customers a monthly rate for the tools we use. We see these tools as necessary to do our jobs and keep our clients safe and secure.  

I am passionate about the way we do business and know that our company’s most valuable possession is our reputation.

Title: Chief Experience Officer
Company Location: 111 W Monroe St Suite 1220, Phoenix, AZ 85003, United States
Company Description:
I founded my company, phx-IT, in 2003 on a simple concept. Most companies and their staff prefer to have an IT person that is PERSONABLE and PRESENT onsite to handle their technology needs. Instead of waiting for problems to arise, we visit each customer at regular intervals throughout the week and handle their needs while onsite. As we’ve grown we’ve scaled this same model to having technicians visit our clients’ offices on a set schedule multiple times each week. We feel that understanding our customers’ technology needs REQUIRES our presence. This doesn’t mean we’re not available to remotely assist. Rather, remote support is added value to each of our customers instead of being the primary service. 

Over the past 10 years IT support companies have gradually been placed into 2 separate categories, Break/Fix and Managed Service Providers. I think there is a better way of doing business. 

The Break/Fix model 
This provides IT support at an hourly rate when a customer has a problem. These providers typically aren’t proactive about preventing problems but tend to be very good firefighters in emergencies.

MSP’s (Managed Service Providers) provide preventative maintenance on systems and charge a fee per server and workstation (or per user). They work almost entirely remotely and are very proactive but charge a higher rate if they ever have to be onsite, which they typically avoid at all costs since their pricing/service model simply doesn’t take into account the value of being onsite.

As we’ve grown, we’ve added all of tools that our competitors use to allow us to provide a high level of service and give us an advantage in the ever changing IT landscape. The major difference is, we don’t charge our customers a monthly rate for the tools we use. We see these tools as necessary to do our jobs and keep our clients safe and secure.  

I am passionate about the way we do business and know that our company’s most valuable possession is our reputation.

Title: Business Owner
Company Location: 625 W Guadalupe Rd Lot B, Gilbert, AZ 85234, United States
Company Description:
Our Mission Statement

Our slogan is "Hire a partner, not just a landscaper"  for good reason.  One major deficiency we recognized in the landscaping industry is that there is very little communication or transparency with landscaping customers especially in the commercial maintenance sector.  We are innovating to change this for the better through technology.  Some of the major challenges we have identified are the following:

•	Lack of property reports
•	Landscape company is not proactive
•	Calls go unanswered
•	Lack of participation in planning
•	Lack of transparency
•	Slow turnaround times
•	Poor customer service
•	Lack of evidence regarding irrigation repairs
•	and the list goes on...

We are arming our technicians in the field with mobile technology that will allow them to capture pictures, notes and precise locations of issues they have identified in the field so that they can be documented and scheduled for resolution by a central dispatch.  This information is then shared in real-time with our board members and property managers so they are continually aware of what is being worked on and when.  We aim to bring landscaping into the 21st century by developing a collaborative mobile platform where Property Management, Landscape Maintenance, and Stakeholder (Board of Director) teams can work together to build a more aesthetic and attractive community.

Join the Team!

Another major challenge we identified is Green Industry professional acquisition and retention.  We are revolutionizing the Green Industry workforce by providing bonus incentives to each and every job level within the company.  We want our employees to have a stake in the success of our company and an opportunity to build a lucrative career.  Reach out to us today if you are looking for an innovative company you can grow with.

Title: LEAD LANDSCAPE DESIGNER
Company Location: 19820 N 7th St, Phoenix, AZ, United States
Company Description:
Moon Valley Nursery is proud to be a family-owned and operated company. We are also a water-wise, eco-friendly, environmentally green company! We were founded in 1995 in a neighborhood north of downtown Phoenix known as “Moon Valley” and now have farming, retail, and landscaping operations throughout the southwest and across three time zones.  

Keeping things simple, our founder and CEO Les Blake began with a small location and the brilliant idea of providing high-quality trees and plants to his customers THE RIGHT WAY! As the customer base grew, so too did the demand for higher quantities and expanded services. 

Moon Valley Nursery thus began offering, “you buy it and we plant it” tree deals. We also started to provide more services such as everything from design through delivery and installation performed by our professional and dedicated nursery staff along with a one-of-a-kind tree warranty!
 
As the grower of its own massive inventory of trees, plants, palms and more, Moon Valley continues to set the industry standard for the highest quality, hardiest, and most aesthetically pleasing products. Over the years, Moon Valley Nurseries has expanded across the Southwest, now featuring retail and growing operations in Arizona, California, Nevada, and Texas.

Recently, Moon Valley Nurseries acquired all inventory, production facilities and assets of Growest Nurseries in Palm Springs and Riverside, California; Glen Flora Farms in Katy Texas; and other well established regional nursery operations.

Moon Valley Nurseries is now the largest grower of box trees and palms in North America.
 
We live by one simple rule:  Bigger trees, better service, and always the best price… Guaranteed!!!

We believe that determination, a talented and qualified staff, and first impressions make all the difference. All Terrain now operates with more than 50 trucks in the field per day. We quickly became the largest lawn service and HOA maintenance and commercial snow removal company in Greeley and are excited about our growth into Fort Collins, Loveland, and everywhere in between.
